!!!
%html
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "http-equiv" => "Content-Type"}/
    %meta{:charset => "utf-8"}/
    %meta{:content => "IE=edge", "http-equiv" => "X-UA-Compatible"}/
    %meta{:content => "width=device-width, initial-scale=1", :name => "viewport"}/
    %meta{:content => "", :name => "description"}/
    %meta{:content => "", :name => "author"}/
    %title Musical Artifacts
    / HTML5 shim and Respond.js IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries
    /[if lt IE 9]
      <haml_loud> javascript_include_tag &quot;https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js&quot;, &quot;https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js&quot; </haml_loud>
    = stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true
    = javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true
    = csrf_meta_tags
  %body#page-top.index
    / Navigation
    %nav.navbar.navbar-inverse.navbar-fixed-top
      .container
        / Brand and toggle get grouped for better mobile display
        .navbar-header.page-scroll
          %button.navbar-toggle{"data-target" => "#bs-example-navbar-collapse-1", "data-toggle" => "collapse", :type => "button"}
            %span.sr-only Toggle navigation
            %span.icon-bar
            %span.icon-bar
            %span.icon-bar
          %a.navbar-brand{:href => '/'}
            = t('_other.name')
            %p.subtitle How to does it work?
        / Collect the nav links, forms, and other content for toggling
        #bs-example-navbar-collapse-1.collapse.navbar-collapse
          %ul.nav.navbar-nav.navbar-right
            %li.hidden
              %a{:href => "#page-top"}
            %li.page-scroll
              %a{:href => "#creation"} 0 - Creation
            %li.page-scroll
              %a{:href => "#access"} 1 - Access
            %li.page-scroll
              %a{:href => "#licensing"} 2 - Licensing
            %li.page-scroll
              %a{:href => "#format"} 3 - Open Format
            %li.page-scroll
              %a{:href => "#documentation"} 4 - Document it

    %header
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            .intro-text
              = about_icon 'music'
              %span.name Musical
              %span.name Artifacts
              %hr.star-light
                %p.skills
                  Helping to catalogue, preserve and free the artifacts you need to produce music.
                %h1.skills
                  But how can you help?


    %section#creation
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            .text-center.star-light
              = about_icon 'microphone'
              %h1 Creation

              %p
                So you created some cool musical resource and want to share it which other artists?

              - @tags.each do |tag|
                =link_to artifacts_path(tags: tag), class: 'btn btn-lg btn-outline btn-dark' do
                  %span.em #
                  = tag

    %section#access.success
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            .text-center.star-light
              = about_icon 'arrow-down'
              %h1 Access

              %p
                First things first, the resource has to be accessible somewhere.
              %a{href: 'https://github.com/lfzawacki/musical-artifacts/wiki/File-Hosting' }
                %i.fa.fa-external-link
                How to host files?

    %section#licensing
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            .text-center.star-light
              = about_icon 'document'
              %h1 Licensing

              %p Think about which rights you grant to the resource's users.
              %p Can they use it commercially? Modify it? Redistribute it?
              %a{href: 'https://github.com/lfzawacki/musical-artifacts/wiki/Open-Licenses'}
                %i.fa.fa-external-link
                Learn about open licenses

    %section#format.success
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            .text-center.star-light
              = about_icon 'unlocked'
              %h1 Open format

              %p
                Make it available in a common and openly documented format.
              %a{href: 'https://github.com/lfzawacki/musical-artifacts/wiki/Open-Formats' }
                %i.fa.fa-external-link
                Learn about open formats

    %section#documentation
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12
            .text-center.star-light
              = about_icon 'chat'
              %h1 Documentation

              %p
                TELL the world where to find your resource and how they can use it!

              %a{href: 'https://github.com/lfzawacki/musical-artifacts/wiki/New-Artifacts'}
                %i.fa.fa-external-link
                Registering new artifacts

    %section#about.success
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12.text-center
            %h2 Shall we start?
            %hr.star-light

          .col-lg-8.col-lg-offset-2.text-center
            = link_to artifacts_path, class: 'btn btn-lg btn-outline' do
              %i.fa.fa-search
              Find what you're looking for

    %footer.text-center
      .footer-above
        .container
          .row
            .footer-col.col-md-4
              %h3 Legal
              %h4
                %a{href: 'https://github.com/lfzawacki/musical-artifacts/wiki/Terms-and-Conditions'} Terms and Conditions

            .footer-col.col-md-4
              %h3
                Contact
                %h4
                  %a{href: '/info/contact'}
                    Contact Us

            .footer-col.col-md-4
              %h3 Elsewhere
              %ul.list-inline
                %li
                  %a.btn-social.btn-outline{:href => 'https://github.com/lfzawacki/musical-artifacts'}
                    %i.fa.fa-fw.fa-github

                %li
                  %a.btn-social.btn-outline{:href => 'https://twitter.com/musartifacts'}
                    %i.fa.fa-fw.fa-twitter

                %li
                  %a.btn-social.btn-outline{:href => 'https://github.com/lfzawacki/musical-artifacts/wiki'}
                    %i.fa.fa-fw.fa-file-text

      .footer-below
        .container
          .row
            .col-lg-12
              %p
                Copyright &copy;
                = t('_other.name')
                = Time.now.year

              %p
                Theme is derived from:
                %a{href: 'http://startbootstrap.com/template-overviews/freelancer/'} Bootstrap Freelancer

    / Scroll to Top Button (Only visible on small and extra-small screen sizes)
    .scroll-top.page-scroll.visible-xs.visible-sm
      %a.btn.btn-scroll-top{:href => "#page-top"}
        %i.fa.fa-chevron-up

    / Plugin JavaScript
    %script{:src => "http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery-easing/1.3/jquery.easing.min.js"}
    %script{:src => "/assets/classie.js"}
    %script{:src => "/assets/cbpAnimatedHeader.js"}
    %script{:src => "/assets/freelancer.js"}

    = render 'application/analytics' if Rails.env.production?